  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1rem;">
    <h1 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); color: #1A2E1A; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">About FishSmithLake.com</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #4a5a4a; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">An independent fishing resource for Lewis Smith Lake, Alabama — built for anglers by people who know the lake.</p>

    <div style="line-height: 1.8; color: #334155;">

      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">FishSmithLake.com is an independent fishing resource for Lewis Smith Lake (Lewis Smith Lake) in northern Alabama. We are not affiliated with Alabama Power, the Alabama DCNR, or any government agency. We exist for one reason: to give Smith Lake anglers accurate, specific, useful information about fishing this lake.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">What Makes Smith Lake Different</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">Lewis Smith Lake isn't a generic Southern reservoir. It's Alabama's deepest lake at 264 feet, one of the clearest bodies of water in the southeastern United States, and a nationally recognized spotted bass fishery. It fishes differently from almost every other lake in the region — and most fishing resources treat it like just another Alabama impoundment. We don't.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">What We Cover</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;"><strong>Species guides</strong> — spotted bass, striped bass, crappie, and catfish, each written specifically for Smith Lake's conditions</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;"><strong>Best fishing spots</strong> — coves, arms, and structure across all three counties</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;"><strong>Live water levels</strong> — real-time data from USGS gauge station 02450250</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;"><strong>Fishing regulations</strong> — Alabama license requirements and Smith Lake-specific rules</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;"><strong>Boat launches &amp; marinas</strong> — public access points across Cullman, Walker, and Winston counties</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;"><strong>Tournaments</strong> — Smith Lake's competitive fishing calendar</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;"><strong>Local news</strong> — automatically updated fishing and lake news</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Our Local Experts</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">We work with people who have spent years on this lake. One of our most referenced local voices is <strong>Justin Dyar</strong> — known around the lake as "Mr. Smith Lake" — a Smith Lake resident and waterfront real estate broker who has been fishing and selling property on the lake since 2006. His local knowledge informs several sections of this site, particularly around lake geography, cove characteristics, and seasonal patterns.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Editorial Standards</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">We take accuracy seriously. Read our full editorial standards at <a href="/editorial-standards" style="color: #2D6A4F;">fishsmithlake.com/editorial-standards</a>.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Contact</h2>
      <p>Corrections, local knowledge contributions, and partnership inquiries welcome: <a href="/contact" style="color: #2D6A4F;">fishsmithlake.com/contact</a></p>

